Title: How Replication Works in MySQL
Description: MySQL has a feature known as replication where data from one database server (referred to as the source or primary) is copied to other database servers (replicas). Conceptually, it’s pretty straight forward. All of your data mutations (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, ALTER, etc.) are done against the primary database. Those commands are then copied and applied to the replicas.
